  "text": "The query flow traces as follows: (1) HTTP handler: `pkg/api/ds_query.go` \u2014 `QueryMetricsV2` receives POST /ds/query, binds the MetricRequest DTO, and calls `queryDataService.QueryData`. (2) Query service: `pkg/services/query/query.go` \u2014 `ServiceImpl.queryData` parses the metric request, routes to `handleQuerySingleDatasource` (or expressions/concurrent), which builds a `backend.QueryDataRequest` and calls `s.pluginClient.QueryData`. (3) Plugin client interface: `pkg/plugins/ifaces.go` defines `Client` (wrapping `backend.Handler`). The concrete client is `pkg/plugins/manager/client/client.go` \u2014 `Service.QueryData` looks up the plugin from the registry and calls `p.QueryData`. (4) Plugin dispatch: `pkg/plugins/plugins.go` \u2014 `Plugin.QueryData` delegates to the backend plugin via `pluginClient.QueryData`. For external gRPC plugins, `pkg/plugins/backendplugin/grpcplugin/grpc_plugin.go` dispatches to `ClientV2.QueryData` in `client_v2.go`, which converts to protobuf, sends the gRPC call, and converts the response back via `backend.FromProto().QueryDataResponse`. For core plugins, `pkg/plugins/backendplugin/coreplugin/core_plugin.go` calls the in-process `QueryDataHandler` directly. (5) Response serialization: back in `ds_query.go`, `toJsonStreamingResponse` wraps the `*backend.QueryDataResponse` in `response.JSONStreaming`, which is defined in `pkg/api/response/response.go` \u2014 `StreamingResponse.WriteTo` uses jsoniter to stream-encode the response (including data frames) as JSON.",
